			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>The Industry:</strong></p>
<p>
Word-of-mouth marketing is the new advertising. &nbsp;Except rather than relying on Mad Men like ad execs, our customers believe that the best form of advertising is happy customers telling good stories about great products. &nbsp;That&#39;s what we call a social endorsement and it&#39;s far more likely to influence people than a fancy superbowl ad.</p>
<p>
<b>The company:</b></p>
<p>
SocialChorus is the leading social word-of-mouth marketing solution for the brands that people love. Our customers use our platform to inspire social advocates and deliver millions of trusted social endorsements across all social channels. &nbsp;Our platform does by combining the power of word-of-mouth with the scale and efficiency of the cloud, to deliver social ROI for our customers.</p>
<p>
We build and deliver everything with our amazing development and solution teams in San Francisco. We&#39;re far enough along to be a real company and early enough to be interesting (post Series-A, pre-Series B funding). We are backed by Kohlberg Ventures and relied on by brands like 3M, Intel, HTC and many others.</p>
<p>
<b>The position:</b></p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.linkedin.com/pub/gal-josefsberg/0/730/728" target="_blank">Gal Josefsberg</a>, our VP Products, is looking for a social media superstar w/ a strong interest in product management. Ideally we&#39;d find someone w/ 1-3 years as a product manager, but depth in social media is our primary need.</p>
<p>
We need someone who&#39;s built, worked with or managed a social site or application so when we ask you questions like &quot;what type of leaderboard should we build?&quot;, &quot;what calls to action work best in social?&quot; or &quot;do images or text work better in social?&quot; you should already know the answer rather than have to research it. &nbsp; That means folks who&#39;ve run social media marketing, program managers who ran advocacy campaigns in an agency or product managers who&#39;ve worked on a social product.</p>
<p>
<b>Projects ready and waiting for you:</b></p>
<p>
<u>Dashboard</u>: We collect an enormous amount of data and we&#39;re looking for better ways in which we can show this data to our customers and their influencers. You&#39;ll work with customer reps and our internal program managers to figure out what works and what doesn&#39;t. You&#39;ll also work with parter programs for most of the major social networks on how to get this information and what it means.</p>
<p>
<u>Gamification</u>: Our brand customers have loyal fans who are willing to act on their behalf, that&#39;s the whole point of Word-Of-Mouth marketing. How do we make these actions fun for them so they&#39;ll do even more? Should we implement badges? Point accumulation? Leaderboards? You&#39;ll survey actual fans and influencers to see what motivates them plus do extensive market research on gamification to see which models are best suited for our needs.</p>
<p>
<u>Facebook Open Graph Data</u>: There&#39;s a lot of data in Facebook, almost too much. Which data points are valuable? Which ones should we collect? How do we get the right data while also being sensitive to the privacy needs of our customers and influencers? This is your chance to become a thoughtleader in an exciting and new space that&#39;s going to be extremely important in the future.</p>
<p>
<b>The details:</b></p>
<p>
This is a full-time, salaried position offering stock options, paid vacation, and benefits: medical, dental, 401k. You&#39;ll be working onsite at <a href="https://maps.google.com/maps?q=703+Market+Street+Unit+470,+San+Francisco,+ca+94103&amp;hl=en&amp;sll=37.269174,-119.306607&amp;sspn=12.126169,26.762695&amp;hnear=703+Market+St+%23470,+San+Francisco,+California+94103&amp;t=m&amp;z=16&amp;iwloc=A" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">our office</a> in San Francisco, CA. We actively promote diversity and encourage all qualified candidates to apply. &nbsp;If you&#39;ve got questions or want tell a corny joke, please send us an <a href="mailto:michael.pope@socialchorus.com" target="_blank">email</a>.</p>
]]></description>
